        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 19 at 9:28PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 928 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Farnsworth, or 8 miles southwest of Perryton, moving southwest at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Waka and Farnsworth.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
